etic energy of consciousness needs to be stirred and rajas-ified and the po=
tential energy of consciousness needs to be withdrawn/reduced, stopped and =
tamas-ified. These two energies are represented by Saraswati and Rudra.
=A0=

To sustain objectification already present in consciousness, the kinetic e=
nergy of consciousness needs to be in a stable and clear equilibrium and sa=
ttv-ified and the potential energy of consciousness needs to be stirred and=
 rajas-ified. These two energies are represented by Lakshmi and Brahma.
=A0=

To end objectification already present in consciousness, the kinetic energ=
y of consciousness needs to be withdrawn/reduced, stopped and tamas-ified a=
nd the potential energy of consciousness needs to be in a stable and clear =
equilibrium and sattv-ified. These two energies are represented by Gouri an=
d Vishnu.
=A0
