daily Chandi homam and invoking Mahalakshmi as the main deity. He was using=
 the dhyana shloka for Mahalakshmi from "Vaikritika Rahasyam" (shvetAnanA n=
IlabhujA sushveta stana maNDalA...). He later switched to a different dhyan=
a shloka - the one for Adyadi Mahalakshmi from whom Mahakali, Mahalakshmi a=
nd Mahasaraswati came - from "Pradhanika Rahasyam" (sarvasyAdyA mahAlakShmI=
H trigunA parameshvarI...), thinking that it was superior.
=A0
His guru tol=
d him after a few months, "whatever dhyana shloka you use, know its meaning=
 and physically imagine someone in that form". He came and asked me for the=
 meaning. I discouraged him, "I don't think you really want to know the mea=
ning and physically imagine someone in that form". When he insisted, I told=
 him the meaning.
=A0
The verses describe Mahalakshmi who is the "First amo=
ng all" (sarvasya AdyA) and having all 3 gunas. She is described as holding=
 in her hands a liquor bowl, snake, male genital, female genital, king's he=
ad etc. Of course, if one starts imagining such a form, it may distract one=
's mind based on one's conditioning!
=A0
*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=
=A0=A0=A0=A0 *
=A0
The thing here is that these symbols represent some subt=
le things. The "Initial Kinetic Energy" from which whole creation came abou=
t obviously works by intoxicating parts of consciousness with notions (liqu=
or bowl), giving rise to notions of gender and identity (male and female ge=
nitals), self-awareness/Kundalini (snake), egosense (king's head) etc. When=
 one is dealing with such Initial or high level energies, concepts become s=
ubtle/abstract. If one wants an explicit outer form, it is better to imagin=
e slightly lower level manifestations with specific gunas and purposes.
=A0=

Let me say it in different words. The Kinetic energy of Purushottama is be=
yond our thoughts, perception and imagination. Various descriptions and ima=
gery in various scriptures are very likely to be misunderstood by us based =
on our conditioning. It's just too hi-fi for foolish and egoistic ignoramus=
es of Kali yuga, like us.
